> Do not use self-bots or user-bots. Each account must be associated with a human, not a bot. Self-bots put strain on Discord’s infrastructure and our ability to run our services. For more information, you can read our Developer Policies here.

**From Discord Developer Policy:**
> You may not mine or scrape any data, content, or information available on or through Discord services (as defined in our Terms of Service).

1) Deploying DiscordChatExporter on Google Cloud Function **FAILED**
> - Firstly, I had to write an entry point script in python that invokes the executables of DiscordChatExporter and pushes the downloaded JSON file to Cloud Storage. Then, I uploaded the script with the executables to GCF.
> -  After a whole day of debugging, the only remaining issue was that GCF never recognized dotnet commands required to invoke the executables. This might be because I had to choose Python runtime for the GCF environment. GCF provides us an option of .Net runtime; however, we will need to write the entry point script in C# to test this possibility. This was a challenge to me, and I stopped the experiment at this point.
> - Note that hosting a Docker container on GCF is not feasible. Instead, Google’s other serverless product, Google Cloud Run, serves this purpose.
